Package io.github.JeremyBloom.mosdex2

Class DisplayWindow

java.lang.Object
io.github.JeremyBloom.mosdex2.DisplayWindow
public class DisplayWindow
extends java.lang.Object
Displays output in a text window. Replaces System.out to separate results output from console output, which can be very crowded and voluminous when using Spark. Enables selecting and copying text to the system clipboard. You can highlight the text either by dragging the mouse or by using the Select All command on the Edit menu. Then the Copy command will copy the selection to the clipboard. Copy is available as an Edit menu item or as a popup.
Author:
Dr. Jeremy Bloom (jeremyblmca@gmail.com)

  • Constructor Details

    • DisplayWindow

      public DisplayWindow​(java.lang.String title)
      Creates a window to display text. The window has a dropdown Edit menu that enables selecting all of the text and copying the selection to the system clipboard. Text can also be selected by dragging the mouse over it. The window also has a popup menu to copy the selected text.
      Parameters:
      title - title to be shown at the top of the window

    • DisplayWindow

      public DisplayWindow()
      Creates a display window with a blank title.

    • printStream

      public DisplayWindow.ExtendedPrintStream printStream()
      Creates an extended PrintStream instance that directs its output to this display window. Enables using all of the PrintStream print(...) and println(...) methods for different types of arguments. Note that using the PrintStream is possibly inefficient due to the need to check updates to the line numbers after writing each character.
      Returns:
      an ExtendedPrintStream instance
